<p>If I have to drone in on semantics (and largely in my defence), the term &quot;Church&quot; usually connotes Christianity. And with a name like &quot;Church of the Broken God&quot;, one would logically assume a wee bit of Christian favour in it (Okay, that is largely my headcanon and I believe that all words and names have meaning in context. Also, I'm not sure if those who coined the term thought of it as such, but there's always headcanon.).</p>
<p>That said, I do admit that the parallels between my article and the Christian story are rather uncanny. But then again, the SCPs involved are Biblical entities.</p>
<p>P.S. I'm not making up the connotations part, even <a href="http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/church?s=t">Dictionary.com</a> says so.</p>

